<DOC><DOCNO> AP880928-0226 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-28-88 2343EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Salvador-HelicopterCrash     09-28 0263</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Salvador-Helicopter Crash,0269</SECOND><HEAD>Five Dead in War Zone Helicopter Crash</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Salvadoran militaryhelicopter crashed Wednesday during evacuation operations in anorthern war zone, killing all five men aboard, the armed forcespress office said.   It said the U.S.-made Bell UH-1H helicopter crashed whileevacuating troops from the vicinity of San Francisco Morazan inChalatenango province, about 46 miles north of San Salvador. It didnot say what caused the crash.   The pilot of another Salvadoran air force helicopter was woundedby rebel fire in northern Chalatenango on Sunday, the army pressoffice said.   A broadcast on the guerrillas' clandestine Radio Venceremos onTuesday said there was heavy fighting in Chalatenango and accusedthe Salvadoran army of the ``indiscriminate bombing'' of a smalltown in the province. It did not identify the town.   The broadcast said rebel forces inflicted 22 casualties ongovernment troops Sept. 21-26. It did not say if there were anyrebel casualties.   Marxist-led guerrillas have waged a 9-year-old war against theU.S.-backed government.   Wednesday's crash was the second this year of an armyhelicopter. In January, a UH-1H helicopter crashed near San JoseGuayabal, about 15 miles north of the capital, killing three menaboard.   The press office identified the dead as Lt. Oscar Arturo MongeVides, the helicopter pilot; Manuel de Jesus Turcios Garcia, theco-pilot and a cadet; two artillery soldiers and an army medic.   Also Wednesday, the armed forces press office reported thatrebel forces attacked a sugar mill in central El Salvador, killingone soldier and wounding another.</TEXT></DOC>